  RG SCALING: How does degree-d energy fraction scale with m?
    Degree 2: fraction ~ m^-1.98
    Degree 4: fraction ~ m^8.98

  PHYSICAL INTERPRETATION:
    The phase transition is a genuine RG crossover.
    Degree-2 (pairwise couplings) = marginal/relevant in UV
    Degree-4 (4-body interactions) = irrelevant in UV, relevant in IR
    Critical point: p ≈ 13 where degree-4 first dominates degree-2
    This is analogous to the Wilson-Fisher fixed point in φ⁴ theory!

===========================================================================
CONNECTION 2: QR ERROR-CORRECTING CODES ↔ TOURNAMENT STRUCTURE
===========================================================================

  p = 7:
    QR set (= Paley connection set): [1, 2, 4]
    NQR set: [3, 5, 6]
    QR code: [7, 4, d ≥ 2]
    Paley codeword weight: 3 = (p-1)/2 = m
    Autocorrelation C(s) = |QR ∩ (QR+s)|:
      C(0) = 3, χ(s) = 0
      C(1) = 1, χ(s) = +1
      C(2) = 1, χ(s) = +1
      C(3) = 1, χ(s) = -1
      C(4) = 1, χ(s) = +1
      C(5) = 1, χ(s) = -1
      C(6) = 1, χ(s) = -1
    PERFECT DIFFERENCE SET: C(s) = 1 for ALL s ≠ 0
    Verified: True

    CODING THEORY LINK:
    The two-valued autocorrelation means the QR code has
    'almost perfect' error-correcting properties.
    This SAME property makes Paley the eigenvector of J:
      J[i,j] depends on QR orbit of (i,j)
      → two-valued → J has only 2 distinct eigenvalues on QR⊥
      → σ_P in the top eigenspace (THM-137)

  p = 11:
    QR set (= Paley connection set): [1, 3, 4, 5, 9]
    NQR set: [2, 6, 7, 8, 10]
    QR code: [11, 6, d ≥ 3]
    Paley codeword weight: 5 = (p-1)/2 = m
    Autocorrelation C(s) = |QR ∩ (QR+s)|:
      C(0) = 5, χ(s) = 0
      C(1) = 2, χ(s) = +1
      C(2) = 2, χ(s) = -1
      C(3) = 2, χ(s) = +1
      C(4) = 2, χ(s) = +1
      C(5) = 2, χ(s) = +1
      C(6) = 2, χ(s) = -1
      C(7) = 2, χ(s) = -1
      C(8) = 2, χ(s) = -1
      C(9) = 2, χ(s) = +1
      C(10) = 2, χ(s) = -1
    PERFECT DIFFERENCE SET: C(s) = 2 for ALL s ≠ 0
    Verified: True

    CODING THEORY LINK:
    The two-valued autocorrelation means the QR code has
    'almost perfect' error-correcting properties.
    This SAME property makes Paley the eigenvector of J:
      J[i,j] depends on QR orbit of (i,j)
      → two-valued → J has only 2 distinct eigenvalues on QR⊥
      → σ_P in the top eigenspace (THM-137)

  DEEP CONNECTION:
    Paley tournament ←→ QR error-correcting code
    H-maximization ←→ ML decoding of received word
    Walsh spectrum of H ←→ weight enumerator of code
    Phase transition ←→ channel capacity threshold
    σ_P as eigenvector ←→ perfect/near-perfect code property

